# OpenAI SDK Cursor Rules

## Chat Completions
- Use `gpt-4o` for quality, `gpt-4o-mini` for speed/cost
- Set `temperature` based on use case: 0 for deterministic, 0.7-1.0 for creative
- Set `max_tokens` to control response length
- Use system messages to set behavior and constraints

## Streaming
- Use streaming for real-time UI updates: `stream: true`
- Process chunks as they arrive with async iteration
- Handle `[DONE]` signal for stream completion
- Implement error handling for mid-stream failures

## Function Calling (Tools)
- Define tools with JSON Schema for parameters
- Use `tool_choice: "auto"` for LLM to decide when to call tools
- Validate tool call arguments before executing
- Return structured results back to the model

## Structured Output
- Use `response_format: { type: "json_schema" }` for guaranteed JSON
- Define response schemas with Zod/Pydantic
- Use for data extraction, classification, structured analysis

## Best Practices
- DO: Implement exponential backoff for rate limits
- DO: Use tiktoken to count tokens before sending
- DO: Cache responses for identical prompts
- DON'T: Send sensitive data without considering privacy
- DON'T: Blindly trust model output — validate and sanitize
- DON'T: Use `gpt-4o` for simple tasks that `gpt-4o-mini` handles well
